\lim_{n\rightarrow\infty} {\int_{1}^{n}\frac{1}{x^{n}} dx} = 0.
x>1
\lim_{n\rightarrow\infty} \frac{1}{x^{n}} = 0.
 \lim_{n \rightarrow \infty} \int_1^n \frac{1}{x^n} dx = \lim_{n \rightarrow \infty} \left[\frac{-1}{(n-1)x^{n-1}}\right]_1^n = \lim_{n \rightarrow \infty} \left[ \frac{-1}{(n-1)n^{n-1}} - \frac{-1}{(n-1)} \right]. 
